Describe a person you know who runs a family business

I'd like to talk about my aunt, who runs a small family-owned grocery store in my hometown. Her name is An, and she's currently in her 50s.
Although I don't see very often these days, I usually visit her store whenver I return home during holidays or special ocassions. Her business has been around for a very long time - probably even before I was born - so it has become quite well-established in the local community.
The store itself isn't very large, but it offers a wide variety of products, ranging from snacks and packaged foods to basic household necessities. Over the years, it has gained a loyal customer base, and I believe most people in my town have shopped there at least once.
What I find particularly impressive is how she manages the business. She now employs several staff members, but she still maintains a very hands-on approach. One of the main reasons for her success is her exceptional customer service. Unlike some shop owners who may seem distant or impatient, she is always warm, friendly, and approachable. She greets every customer with a smile and takes the time to understand their needs.
Moreover, she ensures that her staff follow the same standard of service, as she strongly believes that customer satisfaction is the key to long-term success. Thanks to her dedication and hard work, the store continues to thrive.
Overall, I really admire her for her commitment and positive attitude, and I hope her business will continue to grow in the future.
